invoice_message: The Victorian State Government’s Essential Services Commission (ESC) has approved a change to Gas Distribution pricing effective 1 January 2006.  These charges are imposed by the local gas distribution company who own and maintain the gas pipes and meters in your area and are the same irrespective of which company a customer buys their gas from.  As a result of these changes our gas pricing for 2006 has also changed.  Please be assured that our pricing will always remain amongst the most competitive available and does not affect any applicable discounts for prompt payment, state government concessions or tariff rebates.  More information can be found on the ESC website www.esc.vic.gov.au

The Essential Services Commission (ESC) has approved a change to Network pricing for gas and electricity effective 1 January 2007. These charges are imposed on all Energy Retailers by the local Distribution Company which own and maintain the poles, wires and meters in your area. Additionally changes to the Retail Standing Offer Tariffs for gas and electricity in most areas will take effect from this date. As a result of these changes our gas and electricity pricing will also change from 1 January 2007. Please be assured that our pricing will remain amongst the most competitive available and does not affect our No Risk Offer, any discounts for prompt payment, state government concessions or tariff rebates.
From 2 January 2014, your energy charges have changed as per the notification published in the Victorian Government Gazette no. S 428 on 2 December 2013.

As you may have seen in the media Victorian energy prices are increasing on the 1st January 2011.  This is due to regulated factors outside of our control including approved network price changes and the cost of renewable energy schemes.  Lumo Energy has worked hard to minimise the price increase. You can still continue to enjoy all your current benefits, discounts &/or concessions.  We believe we offer good, competitive value. If you find another genuinely competitive offer, we’ll go all out to match or beat it.
